    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-20T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="1010"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1010">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/7–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-20T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 20, 1954—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 692. Following declarations of French
                    Government have been agreed to by all parties: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Declaration of the Government of the French Republic (reference: Article
                            10 of the final act<note n="1" xml:id="d1010fn1">For text of the draft
                                final declaration (or act), see telegrams <gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                                    >Secto</gloss> 684 and <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss>
                                690, July 20, <ref target="#pg_1474">pp. 1474</ref> and <ref
                                    target="#pg_1480">1480</ref>, respectively.</note>).</p>
                        <p>“The Government of the French Republic declares that it is prepared to
                            withdraw its troops from the territories of Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam
                            at the request of the governments concerned and in periods which will be
                            fixed in agreement with those governments, with the exception of those
                            cases where, by agreement of the two parties, a certain number of French
                            troops may be left at fixed points and for fixed periods.”</p>
                        <p>“Declaration of the Government of the French Republic (reference: Article
                            11 of the final act).</p>
                        <p>“In the settling of all the problems related to the restoration and the
                            strengthening of peace in Cambodia, Laos, and Vietnam, the Government of
                            the French Republic will base itself upon respect for the independence
                            and the sovereignty, the unity and the territorial integrity of
                            Cambodia, of Laos and of Vietnam.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
